message: Focus on cooking individual raw ingredients (vegetables, proteins) with the 'stove' first, they usually become 20 points. Then combine a 'cooked vegetable' with a 'grain' (e.g., rice, wheat, bread, tortilla) for 40 points. You can also combine a 'cooked protein' with a 'grain' for 40 points. The highest scores (80 points) often come from combining a 40-point item (e.g., cooked vegetable-grain combo) with a single 20-point cooked protein. Be very careful not to combine too many items (more than 3 cooked ingredients/grains) as this often results in 'overcomplicated' items with negative values. The 'water' tool tends to decrease value.
